<section id="uixmlfactorytoolbox">
  <title>
    <tag class='attribute'>type</tag>=<quote>toolbox</quote>
    <tag class='element'>factory</tag>s</title>

  <para>
    The contents of a
    <tag class='element'>factory</tag>s of
    <tag class='attribute'>type</tag>=<quote>toolbox</quote>
    specify the
    <ulink url="&link-typedef-x--w-toolboxfactory;"><classname>&ns;::w::toolboxfactory</classname></ulink>
    methods that get invoked when generating the contents of a toolbox
    container:
  </para>

  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	Inherited generic factory methods
      </term>

      <listitem>
	<para>
	</para>
	<blockquote>
	  <informalexample>
	    <programlisting><![CDATA[
<factory type="tools" id="initial-tools">
  <element id="rectangle">
    <radio />
    <appearance>rectangle-appearance</appearance>
    <group>toolbox-group</group>
  </element>
  <element id="square">
    <radio />
    <appearance>square-appearance</appearance>
    <group>toolbox-group</group>
  </element>
</factory>
]]></programlisting>
	  </informalexample>
	</blockquote>
	<para>
	  A toolbox factory contains any element that's valid in a
	  <link linkend="uixmlfactoryelement">generic factory</link>.
	  This creates a new widget in the container.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
</section>

